(Cool roofs and reflective pavements can also reduce heat absorption. A dark roof) Tj
T*
(may become extremely hot in direct sun, while a cool roof reflects more sunlight) Tj
T*
(and emits heat more effectively. This can lower indoor temperatures and reduce air) Tj
T*
(conditioning use. Reflective pavement must be chosen carefully because glare and) Tj
T*
(reflected heat can affect pedestrians. Permeable pavement can help by allowing) Tj
T*
(water to infiltrate, although it must be maintained so pores do not clog.) Tj
T*
T*
(Heat adaptation also depends on emergency planning. Cities can open cooling) Tj
T*
(centers, extend pool and library hours, send alerts in multiple languages, and) Tj
T*
(check on vulnerable residents during heat waves. Transit stops need shade because) Tj
T*
(people waiting for buses may be exposed for long periods. Outdoor workers need) Tj
T*
(rest, water, and schedule adjustments. Schools and sports leagues need heat) Tj
T*
(policies that protect children during extreme conditions.) Tj
T*
T*
(Good heat planning uses data. Satellite temperature maps, tree canopy surveys,) Tj
T*
(hospital records, and resident reports can identify priority areas. The strongest) Tj
T*
(plans combine physical changes, such as shade and cool surfaces, with social) Tj
T*
(programs that reach people before heat becomes deadly. Reducing an urban heat) Tj
T*
(island is not a single project. It is a long-term practice of redesigning streets,) Tj
T*
(buildings, emergency systems, and maintenance budgets around a hotter climate.) Tj
T*
T*
(Public communication is part of adaptation because heat risk is often) Tj
T*
(underestimated. People may prepare for storms more readily than for several) Tj
T*
(extremely hot days, even though heat can be deadly. Cities can publish) Tj
T*
(neighborhood heat maps, name cooling centers clearly, and work with local) Tj
T*
(organizations that residents already trust. When communities understand where heat) Tj
T*
(risk is highest and what help is available, infrastructure investments and) Tj
T*
(emergency response become more effective.) Tj
T*
